// Automatic reboot after an unattended upgrade that requires one (added 2026-07-18).
//
// Before this, unattended-upgrades installed kernels but never rebooted, so a node ran an old
// kernel indefinitely and only picked the new one up during an UNPLANNED restart — which is how
// wk-1 came back on 7.0.0-28 after dying mid-afternoon. Taking the reboot at a known hour is
// strictly better than discovering it at a random one.
//
// STAGGER THE TIME PER NODE so the cluster never loses two at once. In use:
//   wk-1 = 03:30 · wk-2 = 04:30
// prepare-host.sh sets it from UPGRADE_REBOOT_TIME (default 03:30).
//
// NOTE: this does NOT drain the node first — pods are terminated by the kubelet shutting down.
// Acceptable for single-replica workloads with graceful shutdown, but a drain hook is the better
// long-term answer while Postgres is pinned to one node's local storage.
Unattended-Upgrade::Automatic-Reboot "true";
Unattended-Upgrade::Automatic-Reboot-WithUsers "true";
Unattended-Upgrade::Automatic-Reboot-Time "03:30";
